    + Syntax for importing math module: import math
    + Common math module functions:
        Function            |Description            |Function           |Description
        --------------------|-----------------------|-------------------|-----------------------
        # NUMBER REPRESENTATION AND THEORETIC FUNCTIONS
        ceil(x)             |Smallest integer ≥ x   |floor(x)           |Largest integer ≤ x
        factorial(n)        |n! (factorial of n)    |fabs(x)            |Absolute value of x
        fmod(x, y)          |Remainder of x / y     |fsum(x)            |Accurate floating sum
        # POWER, EXPONENTIAL AND LOGARITHMIC FUNCTIONS
        exp(x)              |e^x                    |log(x[, base])     |Logarithm of x to given base
        pow(x, y)           |x raised to power y    |sqrt(x)            |Square root of x
        # TRIGONOMETRIC FUNCTIONS
        sin(x)              |Sine of x (radians)    |cos(x)             |Cosine of x (radians)
        tan(x)              |Tangent of x (radians) |asin(x)            |Inverse sine of x
        atan(x)             |Inverse tangent of x   |atan2(y, x)        |Inverse tangent of y
        hypot(x, y)         |√(x² + y²)             |degrees(x)         |Convert radians to degrees
        radians(x)          |Convert degrees to rad |acos(x)            |Inverse cosine of x
        cosh(x)             |Hyperbolic cosine      |sinh(x)            |Hyperbolic sine
        #COMPLEX NUMBER FUNCTIONS
        gamma(x)            |Gamma function         |erf(x)              |Error function
        # MATHEMATICAL CONSTANTS
        pi                  |3.141592653589793      |e                   |2.718281828459045
        --------------------|-----------------------|-------------------|-----------------------

