Subject -> Style Guidelines
    + Sub-statements are indented four spaces from the main statement.
        - if a < b:
                print("a is less than b")
    + Variable/Parameter and function names are snake_cases starting with lowercase.
    + Constants use upper case and underscores (and at least two words).
        - MAX_SPEED = 100
    + Class names are CamelCase with uppercase first.
        - class StudentRecord: